Sauce Labs Wins Top Workplace and Industry Product Award



Named a 2017 Top Workplace by Bay Area News Group; Also Named SD Times 100 Award Winner for a Second Consecutive Year

/EINPresswire.com/ -- SAN FRANCISCO, CA--(Marketwired - Jun 27, 2017) -  Sauce Labs, Inc., provider of the world's largest cloud-based platform for automated testing of web and mobile applications, today announced it was named a 2017 Top Workplace by the Bay Area News Group, while also winning its second consecutive SD Times 100 Award. The news builds on the momentum generated by the company's first ever user conference, SauceCon, a sold-out event held in San Francisco earlier this month.
"Sauce Labs is delighted to win our first-ever award for our workplace culture," said Charles Ramsey, CEO of Sauce Labs. "We provide a positive, flexible work environment for our employees where we conduct ourselves with respect, integrity and transparency. It's truly an honor to see our focus on creating a great workplace be rewarded in this way."
Sauce was selected as a Top Workplace by the Bay Area News Group based on a rigorous assessment of organizational health and employee feedback. Several aspects including "alignment," "execution" and "connection" were among the criteria considered. More than 6,000 organizations participated in this year's competition.
Sauce was further recognized in the SD Times 100 as a top influencer and leader in the testing category for a second consecutive year. The annual awards program selects innovators in 10 different categories based on each company's offerings, reputation, leadership and "buzz" within their industry. Selected by SD Times editors, the list represents what the experts believe to be "the best of the best."
Sauce Labs provides a high-performance, cloud-based automated testing platform that is optimized for Continuous Integration (CI) and Continuous Delivery (CD) workflows. When tests are automated and run in parallel on virtual machines or real devices, testing time is significantly reduced and IT teams no longer need to devote time to managing testing infrastructure. When paired with a CI system, multiple development teams can instantly provision scalable resources to test web, hybrid, and native applications, continuously and affordably. Sauce Labs currently supports more than 900 browser, operating system, and device combinations.
Didn't make it to SauceCon 2017? Check out playbacks of the sessions here. 
Helpful Links


Sauce Labs website


Sauce Labs blog


Appium website


Twitter 

About Sauce LabsSauce Labs provides the world's largest cloud-based platform for the automated testing of web and mobile applications. Its award-winning service eliminates the time and expense of maintaining an in-house testing infrastructure, freeing development teams of any size to innovate and release better software, faster.
Sauce Labs is a privately held company funded by Toba Capital, Salesforce Ventures, Centerview Capital Technology, IVP and Adams Street Partners. For more information, please visit https://saucelabs.com.



Media Contact:Scott Lechner
Kulesa Faul for Sauce Labs
(530) 521-3095scott@kulesafaul.com






