can't do anything wrong by trying, because it's free.What business problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?Juice Shop is aintentionally insecure Javascript web application designed to be used during security trainings, classes, workshops or awareness demos. It contains over 25 vulnerabilities that an aspiring hacker can exploit in order to fulfill challenges that are tracked on a scoreboard. My end-to-end tests ensure that the overall functionality (e.g., logging in, placing products in the basket, submitting an order, etc.) is working and it performs attacks on the application that should solve all the existing challenges. By running the suite on Sauce Labs I can make sure that Juice Shop works as it should without having to run them locally all the time I push a change to the development-branch. The tests run roughly 2min so it's nice to be able to avoid this kind of "pause" on my laptop and give the job to the Sauce Labs platform instead.Read MoreShare on0 of 0 found this helpful.Helpful?YesNo0 CommentsAdd a CommentAdd a CommentRespond as Sauce LabsReport a Concern1 2 3 4 5 … Next › Last » Learning about Sauce Labs?We can help you find the solution that fits you best.Chat with a G2 advisor+1 (888) 618-0782* We monitor all Sauce Labs reviews to prevent fraudulent reviews and keep review quality high. We do not post reviews by company employees or direct competitors.  Validated reviews require the user to submit a screenshot of the product containing their user ID, in order to verify a user is an actual user of the product.Company: Sauce LabsWebsite: saucelabs.comCategoriesTest AutomationSoftware TestingCompare Sauce Labs to Similar SolutionsSauce LabsvsApplauseSauce LabsvsTestRailSauce LabsvsPerfectoSauce LabsvsQuality CenterSauce LabsvsApache JMeterWhat users like about Sauce LabsCross Browser support+ 29Multiple environments+ 23Reporting and Dashboards+ 17live test management+ 16High Availibility+ 13Supports most popular langu